        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Text Element: items[410412345][fieldname]\r\nWorks perfect if I am just rendering the form normally (ie. echo $this->form; )\r\nThis time around though, I'm doing some more complicated stuff with the form and wanted to control exactly where and how the elements are rendered, so I thought I'd echo the subforms\/elements directly in my view script.\r\n{code}\r\n<?php echo $this->form->items; ?>\r\nworks\r\noutputs <input type=\"text\" name=\"items[410412345][field1].... \/> and so on\r\nany deeper than the first level is where I run into problems\r\n<?php echo $this->form->items->getSubForm('410412345'); \/*since objects don't appreciate numbers*\/ ?>\r\ndoesn't work\r\noutputs <input type=\"text\" name=\"410412345[field1]....\/>\r\n{code}\r\nThe same thing happens with ::getElement('name').  The immediate parent in belongsTo is the only one that is output in the name and id.  \r\nUnless I am missing the correct way to grab the elements, I think it would be useful to have an option to pull in the full name from all the parents up the chain.  I can see where it wouldn't be necessary when rendering a single subform at a time, but when using the nesting to separate pieces of the form and not being able to just render the entire form, it would be great."
        },
