        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41023",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ss10sb",
                        "name": "ss10sb",
                        "displayName": "Scott Morken",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I see now that there is a way to do this using elementsBelongTo and belongsTo (ZF-9451).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ss10sb",
                        "name": "ss10sb",
                        "displayName": "Scott Morken",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-17T12:01:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-17T12:01:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41026",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That would require Zend_Form_SubForm to have a belongsTo member as well,\r\nthat is not the case atm. What is the way you see it?\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-17T12:44:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-17T12:44:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41029",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ss10sb",
                        "name": "ss10sb",
                        "displayName": "Scott Morken",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I would love to see that.  I have a deeply nested set of elements that I finally got to name correctly using the elementsBelongTo property on their immediate subform parent, but that is making for some interesting returns in ::getValues($_POST) since Zend_Form is seeing multiple belongTos and nesting them oddly in the merge -\r\nelement is <input type=\"text\" name=\"items[410412232][30181391][field]\" ...\/>\r\ngetValues is merging the subForms' belongTos on top of array so that I end up with something like:\r\n{code}\r\n'items' => \r\n    array\r\n      'items' => \r\n        array\r\n          410412232 => \r\n            array\r\n              30181391 => \r\n                array\r\n                  'Attendance' => string '' (length=0)\r\n      410412218 => \r\n        array\r\n          'items' => \r\n            array\r\n              410412218 => \r\n                array\r\n                  30181391 => \r\n                    array\r\n                      'Attendance' => string '1' (length=1)\r\n{code}\r\nI was planning to override getValues in my extended form and see if I can get it to drop the extra nesting.  \r\nWith that in mind, I think adding an option to iterate over all the parents would be great. The idea seems easier than what I'm doing above (elementsBelongTo and overriding the ::getValues() to fix the array).  But you know this thing inside and out and know what kind of mess it would make to add that feature. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ss10sb",
                        "name": "ss10sb",
                        "displayName": "Scott Morken",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-17T13:08:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-17T13:08:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41031",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ss10sb",
                        "name": "ss10sb",
                        "displayName": "Scott Morken",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I thought about what you said about adding a belongsTo member to SubForm and decided to give that a shot since my attempt at overriding ::getValues() above was turning into a bigger mess than it was worth.  I can guarantee I've missed some obvious things\/bugs\/disasters in what I did, but I thought I'd pass it on and if there is anything you can use, have at it!  I decided to go with 'parent' as the subForm member and used it to modify the belongsTo properties as needed.  It basically grabs the parent of the previous form\/subform and adds it to the current subform + the current's parent, a simple array.\r\nI extended Zend_Form and Zend_Form_SubForm (only so I could point it at my new Form class so it could pick up the parent property).  I made a small change to Zend_Form_Decorator_FormElements::render method as follows:\r\n{code:title=Zend_Form_Decorator_FormElements|borderStyle=solid}\r\n    \/**\r\n     * Render form elements\r\n     *\r\n     * @param  string $content\r\n     * @return string\r\n     *\/\r\n    public function render($content)\r\n    {\r\n        $form    = $this->getElement();\r\n        if ((!$form instanceof Zend_Form) && (!$form instanceof Zend_Form_DisplayGroup)) {\r\n            return $content;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        $belongsTo      = ($form instanceof Zend_Form) ?\r\n             ( $form->getParentString() !== false ?\r\n               $form->getParentString() :\r\n               $form->getElementsBelongTo() ) :\r\n                    null;\r\n{code}\r\nMy extended files are attached.  Yes I know, \"PC\" isn't Zend legal ;) I know there will be a lot more to it than what I've done here (like adding the toggle to use all the parents or not for multipage), but I hope it is in the right direction!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ss10sb",
                        "name": "ss10sb",
                        "displayName": "Scott Morken",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-17T15:50:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-17T15:50:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41032",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ss10sb",
                        "name": "ss10sb",
                        "displayName": "Scott Morken",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "PC_Form and PC_Form_SubForm files",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ss10sb",
                        "name": "ss10sb",
                        "displayName": "Scott Morken",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-17T15:51:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-17T15:51:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41033",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ss10sb",
                        "name": "ss10sb",
                        "displayName": "Scott Morken",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Oops, overriding _setElementsBelongTo() causes double nesting.  Leaving it as is seems to work perfectly.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ss10sb",
                        "name": "ss10sb",
                        "displayName": "Scott Morken",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-17T16:02:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-17T16:02:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41277",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Postponing, should have for 2.0",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-30T14:24:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-30T14:24:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42347",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ss10sb",
                        "name": "ss10sb",
                        "displayName": "Scott Morken",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Some updated files (finally got around to extending the Zend_Form_Decorator_FormElements class instead of my little hack to the actual Zend file... laziness and procrastination!).  Added a flag to set whether to use the parent form's in the array naming or not (::setUseParent(bool)).  If it is set, it will use the parent's names in the array naming scheme.  If not, it will use only the item being rendered as the parent.\r\n\r\nThere is a problem with it rendering parents correctly when rendering an entire form (<?php echo $this->form; ?> versus rendering the elements through a viewscript (<?php echo $this->element->elementname; ?>). The viewscript rendered elements pick up the parents correctly while the rendered form seems to drop the nesting above the form being rendered.  I haven't had time to look into it and figure out why since I have been using a viewscript when I need the deep nesting anyway. (more laziness and procrastination)\r\n\r\nI thought I would add my 'new' files in case they can help out with building 2.0.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ss10sb",
                        "name": "ss10sb",
                        "displayName": "Scott Morken",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-09-23T07:41:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-09-23T07:41:45.000+0000"
